window.userReviewsJSON = [{"asin":"B081PTN24H","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> Be prepared to laugh out loud. The cupidity books have the most lovable and hilarious FMCs. Trix is just as adorable as ML from heart hassle series. The writing is just so darn witty without being cheesy or cringy. I can’t get enough of the absurdity and cuteness. But the romance… such an absolutely perfect MMC. Such a heart happy fun listen!!! </p>","title":"So fun and swoon worthy"},{"asin":"B0DQF4F1W1","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"1"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"1"}],"summary":"<p> This books is so repetitive. Even if wasn’t the 6th in series to be read in order there is no reason to reiterate how poorly women are treated or their role as mindless whores over and over in every chapter. There is also no real reason given for all of the horrible things the leaders do or make others do. Yeah yeah… power and money. But this one in particular the acts are all way more grotesque and brutal yet far more removed from any reasonable reason. The constant sharing of the clip of Hayden telling his wife how much he loves her is sweet but not enough to make up for the rest of the garbage. <br><br>I think the only reason this book is as popular as it is - is because it is read by Corvin King. He could read me a dictionary and I would be happy. </p>","title":"Horrible"},{"asin":"B0CDXTFMP3","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"1"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"3"},{"name":"Story","stars":"1"}],"summary":"<p> Story had potential but I am not buying anything they characters say or do- it is all just terrible acting in a high school production of a mafia soap opera. The author made a check list of popular catch phrases, spicy scenes, tropes and character types and randomly selected items from each category and dropped them on the page even if they didn’t make sense or flow. Like a copy and paste from 100 other better writer books with the words scrambles a little and is obvious imposter. </p>","title":"Nothing but cliche catch phrases and scenes"},{"asin":"B0FM4HFB42","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> I read this a while ago and it was so good I wanted to read again. There are few books that pack as much raw intensity as this one does right from chapter 1. The narration elevates it to the next level. Of course Joe Arden is incredible as ever but it is Devin Ryder as Tristan that makes this book to a whole new level. Ryders acting is incredible. I feel every single emotion: fury, insecurity, hurt, lust, frustrating, desire, confusion as if they were my own. It doesn’t sound like acting- it is as if he truly is Tristan reacting to everything that is happening. <br><br>The story is beautiful. The rawness of the emotions is incredible. It is concise yet the character depth achieved so quickly is nothing short of brilliant. I understood and fell in love with Tristan within a few paragraphs- sure there is/was plenty more to uncover but I was completely invested in his goals and satisfaction, relief, happiness… I wanted it all for him by the end of the first chapter. And watching the effect he has on Dante is delightfully consuming. </p>","title":"Absolute perfection writing and narration"},{"asin":"B0F9B6B2HT","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> Sierra Simone is the queen of longing and desire, sensual and scorching spice. The new narration is absolute top notch next level perfection. This is my favorite spicy series!! </p>","title":"So hot! So captivating!"},{"asin":"1774248255","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> So good. Haven’t cried this hard from any book, movie, tv show. It is the kind of book that will stay with me for a very long time. Audio is perfection that easily elevates the book 10x. If I could I would give this book 6-7 stars just for being so blindsided by emotions. </p>","title":"Absolutely wrecked me"},{"asin":"B09CLL29V6","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"2"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"2"},{"name":"Story","stars":"2"}],"summary":"<p> This book feels like it skipped any kind of editing. There are so many repetitive chapters. Kind of like when you have long series and each book repeats some of the important details for the previous books in the first couple chapters… except this book is repeating the same details every few chapters. It also slips from first person to third person a few times mid paragraph. <br><br>There is very little spice for having 5 guys. The spice is poorly written. There is maybe one short scene that was hot but the rest were almost as if the author was glossing over what happened- almost matter of facts.<br><br>The female narrator was ok for delivering snarky comments and whatever the characters were saying out loud but for everything else it was very matter of fact with annoying repetitive cadence and inflections. </p>","title":"Repetitive and no spice"},{"asin":"B0D46211XP","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> This series has taken top spot for me. From the first scene in book 1 to where is ended is such a surprise. This series has one of the most satisfying conclusions. The character growth and strength is inspiring. I wouldn’t change a thing about the MMC and MFC or their journey. The minor supporting characters are also amazing. The worlds are beautifully build. The VA / narration is next level. Lilly Drake and Anthony Palmini are some of the best out there for sure. They really take this series to the next level with the heart and soul they put into their work. </p>","title":"BEST MMC and MFC ever"},{"asin":"B0D46BTHX1","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> I love this series. The character development and world building expand even further in this book. There are even more new character POV and things get really suspenseful as a result. <br><br>The vengeance in this series - especially in this book is epic!<br><br>The first few chapters were some of my favorites as the world building was so beautiful and emotional experienced were so immersive good. It is the kind of escapism I am looking for in every book. <br><br>The growth of the MFC is so incredible and it makes me so happy for her. <br><br><br><br>The audio is amazing!!! Lilly Drake and Anthony Palmini are prefect!!! Lilly brings so much emotion. You feel all the sadness, longing, anger, rage, joy, kindness, playfulness right down to the bone. Anthony is so indecently decadent, toe curling sexy. </p>","title":"Epic vengeance"},{"asin":"B0D4616M4P","ratings":[{"name":"Overall","stars":"5"},{"name":"Performance","stars":"5"},{"name":"Story","stars":"5"}],"summary":"<p> I love this series. The character development and world building really take off in this book. The new character POV keeps things really interesting. This series continues to break my heart over and over again every time it stitches it back together. I love that MFC saved herself in book 3 and that she totally calls out the MMC. This book like the last one has an amazing ending but with an even bigger cliff hanger.<br><br>The audio is amazing!!! Lilly Drake and Anthony Palmini are prefect!!! Lilly brings so much emotion. You feel all the sadness, longing, anger, rage, joy, kindness, playfulness right down to the bone. Anthony is so indecently decadent, toe curling sexy. I love the spice in this series the dirty talk and slightly less vanilla aggressiveness is sensational. </p>","title":"The world and character dev really opens up"}];